		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: How to determine polarity of potential Famicom power sup</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The first reading, where you got a non-negative voltage, shows the polarity. Black in center = negative, red on outside part = positive. So it's negative tip, which was the way power adapters were until many years ago, then they started going to positive tip.<br /><br />NOW, this assumes you have the black one plugged into common/gnd on the meter (on yours it's the lowermost plug COM).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


